<br>
Almost never. Since the clerics are rotating CHs and quick heals on one tank and casting group heals when we're facing AE mobs. Last few weeks, my online time has consisted only of HoT and Kael raids. And to give some perspective, Nagafen quads 250sh and AEs. Vehement wyvern quads 330, at twice the speed of Nagafen, an ancient guardian wurm doubles for 390 and casts 2 different AEs and CHs. And those two mobs are just regular mobs in HoT. But both of such mobs can be done with 2 groups (Nagafen was done with one group before level limit), when cleric(s) need to concentrate on one meat shield instead of tossing fast heals here and there. CHing (400 mana) a tank with 5500+ hitpoints or tossing divine lights (350 mana / 950 Heal) here and there...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What I suspect is that the 'one tank taunts' theory only holds true for the highest level of encounters, the rest it isn't as much of an issue<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
From regular xp groups to multi-group raids... it is far more efficient for one person to get healed and others to deal damage without taking it. And this holds true from level 20sh to 60. In pre-20, almost any class can tank equally and heals aren't that refined yet. But I guess you can do raids with zergling rushes and let everyone taunt, I just don't understand why you would want to. I prefer doing those encounters with as small group as possible, in order to retain some excitement there.<br>
<br>
Taunt doesn't add to your aggro. It simply places you to spot one on hate list. So if you are on spot one already, taunting does absolutely nothing. And that's the reason why in normal fight I don't even taunt at all... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
A wizard can blast very much when main tank has the aggro. Even in single group setting. It just need a good main tank with good wizard. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-myz<br>
<br>
PS. We can't mez the adds anymore... there are tons of ways to deal with them. <p>BR,<BR>
