<br>
The whole idea of one mob at a time is just silly in my book. Yes there are time where that is the only way to do it, like mobs that share the wealth (AEs) and MOBs that are just totally Uber (Dragons, etc...) But a group operating correctly can grind through many MOBs at once continuously. It's all in correct group mechanics. <br>
<br>
We got to the one mob at a time because it was easy, and because it made sense. Harmony the Orc camp, pull them out one at a time and kill them. Sure! Why not, I mean, when the orc camp runs out of orcs, you sit, wait for them to spawn one at a time and kill them, no more hard work to get one at a time. We learned something that worked, and kept it close and NEVER let it go.<br>
<br>
But, something doesn't seem right. I mean we decide that we can kill one red at a time this way because the melee types can all hit it, and the healers can heal the melee types. The Pet's are hitting it as well, they are useful, but the Mage/Necro/Enchanter/Wizzy soon learns that actually trying to cast a spell on that red mob is a nearly pointless waste of mana. <br>
<br>
Ohh NO! too many ... CHANTER! So the chanter fixes it (maybe a necro at higher levels) and boom, a couple of classes are totally useless in a group cause one red at a time is the only way.<br>
<br>
And we run off and earn experience by killing 4 at a time. Then we figure out that with the right people, we can kill 4 at a tie in a group using similiar tactics. Hell, we can do 7 at at time that way, or more.<br>
<br>
There is no reason to kill one at a time unless we are hell-bent on pulling reds. There is no reason yet for that. When I'm in a good solid multi-blue exp group, we pull non-stop for hours never needing to med. TOTALLY safe. No deaths and on overpulls because there really is no such thing. Just learn to manage what you do right. CoF; target puller; 4 Mobs eat 214 damage each, MUCH better than 318 on one. I'm on their lists, but not at the top unless I did something wrong. I wait a little while, do it again. Now every mob is dow by 33% of HP and the melee types have probably finished off the one they were on in the first case. They're not getting beaten to death because the creatures are having a hard time getting through the AC and Dodge seems to work, etc... As soon as the last one goes down, pull more. <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Advanced Slayer, WurnSlayer<BR>
Assigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=422.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=399.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=371.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.threadControl?topicID=371.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=371.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=371.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm27">PVP Forum<option value="graffeswiza